deck: A 2013 Valiant Entertainment Crossover.
description:
To kill a king…he has created an army. The world’s most dangerous man, Toyo Harada, has been struck by the one thing he never thought possible – fear. Halfway across the globe, a new power threatens to topple modern civilization and, to preempt the cataclysm that is to come, Harada will unite the most lethal, most volatile, most unforgiving team the world has ever known – UNITY. Their mission: defeat the warrior king armed with the universe’s most powerful weapon. Kill X-O Manowar!

Included Volumes

  • Unity #1-4
  • X-O Manowar #19-22
name: Unity

deck: John Layman's final arc on Detective Comics where Gotham is a bright and shiny place.
description:
Overview

Gothtopia is John Layman's final arc on Detective Comics with various Batman books tying in. In Gothtopia, things in Gotham are very different, such as Catwoman becoming Batman's sidekick "Catbird," and the city is a much happier place for a mysterious reason. Alongside the main storyline in Detective Comics, Batgirl, Catwoman, Batwing and Birds of Prey will be tying into Gothtopia.

deck: Crossover between Batman/Superman and Worlds' Finest, in which Earth-2's Huntress & Power Girl come face to face with Earth-1's Batman & Superman for the first time.
description:
The "First Contact" crossover runs through the February/March 2014 issues of Batman/Superman and World's Finest. After a clash with Desaad leaves Power Girl's abilities malfunctioning badly, Huntress brings her to Earth-1's Batman and Superman for help, marking the first meeting of the two teams. Batman is stunned when he learns that Huntress is his daughter with Catwoman in another universe, while Superman tries to help a cousin he's never met before. Meanwhile, Kaizen Gamorra schemes against the four heroes.

Non-U.S. Editions

  • Batman/Superman #3 (German)
name: First Contact

deck: 2014 story arc in Avengers by Jonathan Hickman and Esad Ribic
description:
Description

Written by Jonathan Hickman and art by Esad Ribic, Rogue Planet is a five issue story arc in Avengers, following Infinity.

Plot Summary

Avengers #24

The Avengers are given a warning from the future when the grandchild of Tony Stark travels back in time, telling him that a rogue planet is on a collision course with the planet earth. They manage to fuse the planet with the earth, giving them a power source and a weapon, which they will need at some point in the near future.
name: Rogue Planet

deck: Batman is accused of killing Talia by shooting her in the back. In his hunt for the truth; he encounters her father, Ra's Al Ghul, who claims to be behind it all and not only frames The Dark Knight for her murder, but his as well. He also runs afoul of The Creeper and Sterling Silversmith before resolving the mystery of the smoking gun.
name: Bat murderer
